 and move all the windows out into the black border. Probably the only mod I might take advantage of is making the buff view horizontal rather then vertical (which I don't think you can just move like you could in the original full screen mode? (forgot to try last night)). I also don't like the spell book button right below the spell gems as it is now. It looks to much like a spell gem and I can see clicking the wrong spell gem because I counted up from the bottom rather then down from the top and I counted the spell book as the 8th gem. Maybe I will see if I can move that off that window entirely. I would still prefer to use old windows mode with just a few small changes (i.e. 10 hot buttons rather then 6) but since they are eventually going to make everyone use the new interface (like it or not) I figured I might as well get used to it. <p><br><br><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=127031" target="_blank"><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bhoward3/images/dadalan.jpg" height=85 width=468 alt="Dadalan Lyfrender" border=0></a></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>591</b>  </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uinienofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inien of Vazaelle</A> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Caster Elder</span><br> </td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title> Re: Rate the interface.</span><br><span class=m><font color=#778899>Posted: 7/25/02 12:16:21 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <hr size=1> There's a master fade setting in the options menu -&gt; display tab.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Set that to 100% and all windows (save the containers, think they have their own setting you have to set seperately) will obey that fade setting unless set otherwise.  Oh, and the buff window, can be moved, expanded, shrunk, resized, reshaped, closed, minimised, etc.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
